.TH "ide_dev_read_id" 9 "ide_dev_read_id" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ide_dev_read_id \- send ATA/ATAPI IDENTIFY command
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ide_dev_read_id
.BI "(ide_drive_t *drive "  ","
.BI "u8 cmd "  ","
.BI "u16 *id "  ","
.BI "int irq_ctx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drive" 12
drive to identify
.IP "cmd" 12
command to use
.IP "id" 12
buffer for IDENTIFY data
.IP "irq_ctx" 12
flag set when called from the IRQ context

Sends an ATA(PI) IDENTIFY request to a drive and waits for a response.
.SH "RETURN"
0  device was identified
1  device timed-out (no response to identify request)
2  device aborted the command (refused to identify itself)
